# SRFetchResult

**Class**

Recorded data that a sensor reader fetches.

## Declaration

```swift
class SRFetchResult<SampleType> where SampleType : AnyObject
```

## Overview

A sensor reader’s [doc://com.apple.sensorkit/documentation/SensorKit/SRSensorReader/delegate] receives instances of this class from the [doc://com.apple.sensorkit/documentation/SensorKit/SRSensorReaderDelegate/sensorReader(_:didCompleteFetch:)] when a fetch request finishes successfully.

Results are in the form of samples, which are of varying types depending on the reader’s sensor. For a list of sample types per sensor, see [doc://com.apple.sensorkit/documentation/SensorKit/SRFetchResult/sample#Sample-types].

## Sampling Data

- **sample**: A recording that the sensor reader fetches.
- **timestamp**: The time when the framework records the sample.

## Querying data

- **SRFetchRequest**: An object that defines the criteria for a sample query.

## Inherits From

- NSObject

## Conforms To

- CVarArg
- CustomDebugStringConvertible
- CustomStringConvertible
- Equatable
- Hashable
- NSCopying
- NSObjectProtocol
